dcterms:description: Elvis is a planning and management tool for electric vehicle charging infrastructure that enables the modeling of the stochastic nature of wind and solar power generation and demand fluctuation of customer agents, implementing demand-side management programs for customer agents. It generates a list of EV charging events specifying arrival time, departure time, state of charge (SoC) at arrival, and vehicle type.
dcterms:title: Elvis

dcterms:description: Renewables Ninja provides simulated hourly power output from wind and solar PV farms based on specific technology and location, allowing for the generation of renewable energy profiles.
dcterms:title: Renewables Ninja

dcterms:description: Pecan Street Dataport provides day-ahead prices for energy markets, allowing for analysis of energy pricing and consumption patterns.
dcterms:title: Pecan Street Dataport

dcterms:description: The Low-Voltage Load Forecasting dataset contains time series of energy consumer/prosumer’s electricity readings and timestamps, providing insights into household energy consumption patterns.
dcterms:title: Low-Voltage Load Forecasting
